    {
      "id": "b43b09a8-fbbe-4625-bd4e-4c44f1453b67",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $\\forall(k,n)\\in(\\Nn^*)^2,\\;[k\\wedge n=1\\Rightarrow n|C_n^k]$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall(k,n)\\in(\\Nn^*)^2,\\;[k\\wedge n=1\\Rightarrow n|C_n^k]\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a46dcd70-6202-49f6-a2bb-d498e6ed331b",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Pour $1\\leq k\\leq n$, $kC_n^k=nC_{n-1}^{k-1}$. Donc, si $k$ et $n$ sont premiers entre eux, puisque $n$ divise $kC_n^k$, le théorème de \\textsc{Gauss} permet d'affirmer que $n$ divise $C_n^k$.",
        "html": "<p>Pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(1\\leq k\\leq n\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(kC_n^k=nC_{n-1}^{k-1}\\)</span>. Donc, si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(k\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> sont premiers entre eux, puisque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> divise <span class=\"math inline\">\\(kC_n^k\\)</span>, le théorème de <span class=\"smallcaps\">Gauss</span> permet d’affirmer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> divise <span class=\"math inline\">\\(C_n^k\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "3be2ed63-21a7-4c4c-adce-5a6d26929d43",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $\\forall n\\in\\Nn^*,\\;(n+1)|C_{2n}^n$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall n\\in\\Nn^*,\\;(n+1)|C_{2n}^n\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2983b125-52cd-4856-a73a-f69fd69af977",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "De même, $(n+1)C_{2n}^{n-1}=nC_{2n}^{n}$ montre que $(n+1)$ divise $nC_{2n}^{n}$ et, puisque $n$ et $(n+1)$ sont premiers entre eux (d'après \\textsc{Bezout} puisque $(n+1)-n=1$), $(n+1)$ divise $C_{2n}^{n}$ d'après le théorème de \\textsc{Gauss}.",
        "html": "<p>De même, <span class=\"math inline\">\\((n+1)C_{2n}^{n-1}=nC_{2n}^{n}\\)</span> montre que <span class=\"math inline\">\\((n+1)\\)</span> divise <span class=\"math inline\">\\(nC_{2n}^{n}\\)</span> et, puisque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\((n+1)\\)</span> sont premiers entre eux (d’après <span class=\"smallcaps\">Bezout</span> puisque <span class=\"math inline\">\\((n+1)-n=1\\)</span>), <span class=\"math inline\">\\((n+1)\\)</span> divise <span class=\"math inline\">\\(C_{2n}^{n}\\)</span> d’après le théorème de <span class=\"smallcaps\">Gauss</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
  "preview": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall(k,n)\\in(\\Nn^*)^2,\\;[k\\wedge n=1\\Rightarrow n|C_n^k]\\)</span>.</p>\n"
